item.title: U.S. Pushes EU to Back China Inquiry
item.description: The Trump administration wants the European Union to support an international inquiry into China’s handling of the pandemic, as Brussels seeks to avoid taking sides.

item.title: ECB Faces Renewed Legal Pressure Over Bond Purchases
item.description: Germany’s highest court conditionally approved a bond-buying program launched five years ago by the ECB but demanded more information about its economic justification, in a move that could set limits on the bank’s firepower.

item.title: Coronavirus Timeline Is Upended as France Discovers December Case
item.description: French doctors have discovered a case of the new coronavirus dating from late December in a man who was hospitalized near Paris, the earliest publicly identified Covid-19 infection outside China.

item.title: U.K. Tests Contact-Tracing App
item.description: The British government rolled out a contact-tracing app on the Isle of Wight as the first step in a new national approach to stem the spread of the new coronavirus.

item.title: In Russia, Putin Wrestles With Economic Impact of Coronavirus
item.description: What was tipped to be a marquee year for the Russian leader has turned into one of the toughest challenges of his 20-year reign.

item.title: Saudi Arabia, Hit With Oil Collapse and Pandemic, Tosses Lifelines
item.description: The kingdom’s unprecedented stimulus measures to cushion the blow of collapsed oil prices and the coronavirus pandemic will force it to cut spending on its transformation away from oil.
